column39:
======================
Problem:
======================

We got high number of resources created in authorization service in the same client ~= 20000++

When no setting resource type, everything is working fine, but when X resources are associated to the same resource type, the request time to get resource details increase as X does .
For instance with 10000 resources with the same type, the request takes approximatively 10 seconds compared to less than 200ms when no resource type is set.


======================
Bug identification:
======================

We identified the bug in the following module:
_server-spi-private/src/main/java/org/keycloak/models/utils/ModelToRepresentation.java_
function on line 794:     

{code:java}
public static ResourceRepresentation toRepresentation(Resource model, ResourceServer resourceServer, AuthorizationProvider authorization, Boolean deep)
{code}


the problem is located into the following block of code :


{code:java}
	if (resource.getType() != null) {
	    ResourceStore resourceStore = authorization.getStoreFactory().getResourceStore();
	    for (Resource typed : resourceStore.findByType(resource.getType(), resourceServer.getId())) {
	        if (typed.getOwner().equals(resourceServer.getId()) && !typed.getId().equals(resource.getId())) {
	            resource.setTypedScopes(typed.getScopes().stream().map(model1 -> {
	                ScopeRepresentation scope = new ScopeRepresentation();
	                scope.setId(model1.getId());
	                scope.setName(model1.getName());
	                String iconUri = model1.getIconUri();
	                if (iconUri != null) {
	                    scope.setIconUri(iconUri);
	                }
	                return scope;
	            }).filter(scopeRepresentation -> !resource.getScopes().contains(scopeRepresentation)).collect(Collectors.toList()));
	        }
	    }
	}
{code}

We don't really understand the aim of this block and especially the `typedScope` attribute of the returned resource.

  - First it iterates over thousands of resources and make almost as many SQL requests due to the call of the instruction `typed.getScopes()` (VisualVM helped us to identify this point)

  - Secondly, resource attribute `typedScopes` is overrided at almost every iteration.

  - Finally, it seems the attribute `typedScopes` is only used by the admin evaluation result page and we should not do this big work everytime we read a resource.


=====================
Our solution while waiting for a fix
=====================

While waiting the version that will fix this algorithm, we will use the URI field to store our types because we don't really need it.
We prefer to wait for an official version with a fix instead of making our own patch.

