15/Sep/17 11:28 AM;jh409;I've gotten around the issue by using the 'check-sso' value for onLoad in Keycloak.init(). I've moved this back to before the bootstrap calls in main.ts and then added an AuthGuard to all my routes which require auth:



{code:javascript}
export class AuthGuard implements CanActivate {

  constructor(private keycloakService) {}

  canActivate() {
    if (this.keycloakService.authenticated()) {
      return true;
    }

    this.keycloakService.login();
    return false;
  }
{code}

app.component.ts's ngOnInit fires before the routing occurs, so rather than move all of my data calls in to subcomponents, which I suspect is the cleaner solution, I've just wrapped them in a conditional which calls the AuthGuard.

I don't find this to be particularly inefficient - the AuthGuard's canActivate() function is called once when the route changes and only ends up making a call to Keycloak.auth.authenticated.

I'm afraid I don't know about parseHash, hopefully [~preetham1290] knows more.

