column39:
We found that we use some incorrect  configuration in the Integrating Red Hat Process Automation Manager with Red Hat Single Sign-On [documentation|https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_process_automation_manager/7.1/html/integrating_red_hat_process_automation_manager_with_red_hat_single_sign-on/] and we have to check it and do so some updates.

First thing we need to update is:

{code:java}
org.uberfire.ext.security.management.api.userManagementServices=KCCredentialsUserManagementService
{code}

should be replaced with:

{code:java}
org.uberfire.ext.security.management.api.userManagementServices=KCAdapterUserManagementService
{code}

[~roger600] could you please check the documentation and write some notes if there anything else what need to be fixed. Thanks.

We need to support a range of versions for backward compatibility

We are going to support:
* A filtered resource that will replace take the list of valid versions from kie-parent pom.xml
* An environment variable that will contain a comma-separated list of supported versions. Those versions will be appended to list declared in kie-parent pom.xml


h2. Example:
{code:xml}
<org.kie.validation.dependency.versions>
7.0.1-redhat-8,7.0.2-redhat-10
</org.kie.validation.dependency.version>
{code}

{code:bash}
*-Dorg.kie.validation.dependency.versions=7.0.1-redhat-8,7.0.2-redhat-10*
{code}

